doc.after: Ireland has a wealth of structures 133 surviving in various states of preservation from the Neolithic period such as Br na B inne Poulnabrone dolmen Castlestrange stone Turoe stone and Drombeg stone circle 134 As the Romans never conquered Ireland architecture of Greco Roman origin is extremely rare The country instead had an extended period of Iron Age architecture 135 The Irish round tower originated during the Early Medieval period
